    <note>Zhang(1) Shengqing [275] Zonggu(2)'s [7170] son, Tingqing's [7167] brother, Xiangzhong's [226] grandson, Kangguo's [248] father, and brother of Qian(1) Xie's [145] wife. His mother was the sister of Qian(1) Yanyuan [7010], therefore his maternal grandfather was Qian(1) Yi [146]. Qian(1) Yanyuan [7010] was Shengqing's father-in-law and the grandfather of his son-in-law, Qian(1) Luwang [4150]. According to his wife's funerary inscription, the Zhang and Qian were a hereditary intermarried group (shiyin) for three generations. He was cashiered for offense against the tea laws. XCB, 289.12b-13a, 400.6b; Guangdong TZ, 15.4b; SHY:ZG, 66.35a-35b; Su Song, WJ, 62.7b, 9a (wife, born Qian Shi, who died in 1081 at age 50). CBD, 3, pp. 2357-8.</note>
